<p>Rio de Janeiro authorities carried out a large, coordinated operation on Tuesday against the Red Command drug gang in the Penha and Complexo do Alemão favela complexes, leaving at least 64 people dead and prompting calls for investigations . Officials described the operation as aimed at curbing the gang&#x27;s territorial expansion and said it was the deadliest police action in Rio state history . Human rights groups and observers demanded independent probes into the killings as the city prepares to host events linked to the UN&#x27;s COP30 climate summit later this week .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/pYtU1WklmF-IpwudqGQkcNg5_SZh9S2nWAtpje1bs3Nyrtm_rK4NKXFNxDzj4JcnIKJ1kfbBUqH6PxFUrPsmIsOt5qSXN12WW4DlQFQAH05h6T0clrVrP8Y-z1t3MwczjSR-hXXWZ4IrFL0Xp8Z2js7f05ix8WKcNPj2drHt3-tbOrqGwHmimFd6i6ijvnGl8-hWDOKAYDBDN9Uv' alt='Police officers with people detained during a drug gang sweep on Tuesday in Rio de Janeiro.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Scale of force: Authorities deployed a large force of police and soldiers — around 2,500 personnel took part in the operation, backed by armoured vehicles and helicopters .</li><li>Arrests made: Officers arrested about 81 people during the raids in the two favela complexes, according to official counts reported by multiple outlets .</li><li>Police casualties: Four police officers were among those killed in the clashes, a fact highlighted in coverage of the operation&#x27;s toll .</li><li>Urban warfare: Reporters described intense street fighting with heavy gunfire and smoke billowing across neighbourhoods, disrupting daily life and transport near parts of the city .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>State government / governor: Authorities framed the raids as a targeted assault on organised crime, saying they sought to dismantle the Red Command&#x27;s territorial expansion and calling the operation necessary for public safety. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/28/world/brazil-rio-de-janeiro-police-drug-raids-deaths.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>Human rights organisations: Groups urged independent investigations into the deaths and questioned the use of lethal force during the raids, calling for transparency and accountability. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/29/brazilian-police-raid-on-rio-drug-trafficking-gang-leaves-at-least-64-people-dead'>Euronews</a>)</li><li>Local residents and witnesses: Residents reported intense exchanges of gunfire, smoke and scenes of bodies in the streets, describing the operation as the most violent they had seen in years. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3330691/over-60-killed-massive-drug-raids-brazils-rio-de-janeiro'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c8x155engwpo'>At least 64 killed in Rio&#x27;s largest police raid on gangs</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1oiqtfx/huge_brazilian_raid_on_rio_gang_leaves_at_least/'>Huge Brazilian raid on Rio gang leaves at least 64 people dead and 81 under arrest.</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/at-least-18-suspects-killed-in-rio-anti-drug-raid-governor'>At least 64 killed in Rio drug raids</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627082-police-raid-in-rio-de-janeiro-64-dead/'>Police raid in Rio de Janeiro leaves 64 dead (VIDEOS)</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/28/world/brazil-rio-de-janeiro-police-drug-raids-deaths.html'>At Least 64 Dead in Rio de Janeiro as Brazilian Police Crack Down on Drug Gangs</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/video/2025/10/29/major-rio-police-raid-leaves-60-suspects-dead'>Major Rio police raid leaves 60 suspects dead</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/brazil-at-least-64-killed-in-major-rio-drugs-raid/a-74530642'>Brazil: At least 64 killed in major Rio drugs raid</a> - dw.com</li><li><a